  "prompt": "Why isn't Snoop Dogg arrested for smoking marijuana?",
  "response": "Snoop Dogg is often seen smoking marijuana in public and in his music, but he hasn't faced significant legal consequences largely due to the changing legal landscape around cannabis in the United States. Many states have legalized marijuana for recreational use, and Snoop Dogg has been a vocal advocate for legalization. \n\nIn states where cannabis is legal, individuals can use it without the fear of arrest, provided they adhere to the regulations regarding usage and possession. Additionally, Snoop Dogg is a celebrity and public figure, which can sometimes affect the way law enforcement treats similar actions. It's also worth noting that law enforcement may choose not to pursue charges in many cases, especially if the individual is compliant and not causing any disturbance.\n\nOverall, Snoop Dogg's prominence, the evolving marijuana laws, and perhaps a degree of leniency toward him due to his status likely contribute to why he hasn't faced arrest for smoking marijuana.",
